description:
About us:  BetterMe is a #1 Health&Fitness publisher in the world in terms of installs and grossing for 2019 according to Appannie. For the last year and a half, BetterMe was downloaded more than 50 million times, on both iOS and Android. We also have the largest health and fitness app community on Facebook, with over 5 million women. Our apps have an average rating of 4.5* in the App Store. All this became possible through a team of 100 talented world-class professionals from Kyiv. 


We are the largest partner of Facebook, Google, Snapchat, and Twitter from CIS. We have extensive experience in user acquisition / analytics / ROI calcs, and we work with highly advanced technologies.  


Our mission is to help people create happiness within, and we achieve it by analyzing client’s behavior, creating personalized data profiles, and ensuring a reliable and long-lasting relationship between us.  


There are 500 million people in the world who value a healthy lifestyle, and we believe that every one of them should be a BetterMe customer. We plan to capture the growth of the Global Health Market, and our ideal candidate focuses on building the largest Health company in the world.  
About you:  About 2 years of experience in a product company working with data analytics; 

Analytical mindset; ability to structure information and dive deeper when it is needed; 

Experience with data visualization tools, BI techniques (Tableau); 

Full proficiency in SQL and Excel; 

Programming experience in Python is a must; 

Strong English written/verbal communication skills. 

Will be a plus: 

Experience with 3rd party product analytics systems (e.g. Amplitude, Facebook Analytics, Firebase, AppsFlyer); 

Experience with A/B testing. 

h4>Your impact: 


Primarily work with Marketing team and help to make correct data-informed decisions; 
Evolve data analytics processes and architecture; 
Develop standardized dashboards and ad hoc reports to inform decision making; 
Participate in improving the internal business intelligence system that consolidates financial data (we call it BetterBI). 
With your thoughts, our business will reach new heights and will make our users even healthier, sportier, happier and better :)  
At the end we finish:  


You will be working with a professional and motivated team of enthusiasts in the environment that brings up best in everyone. We have no bureaucracy, and we give our colleagues complete freedom to make decisions and achieve brilliant results.  


“One last thing”. Naturally, we provide you with everything you need to stay focused on what’s important:  


Competitive salary that will help you focus on your projects and personal development. 
Professional growth. Our Development team is Middle (10%) and Senior (90%) Professionals only. Frequent internal courses and seminars, corporate library, English lessons, and the ability to attend critical events worldwide. 
Comfortable work environment. A spacious office with a summer terrace located within a  
  5-minute 
 walk from Taras Shevchenko metro station, complimentary lunches, Sony PlayStation 4, and other goodies. We will provide you with all the necessary equipment for you to be comfortable and perform well. 
Flexible work hours. You decide your work hours. 
Sport and Fitness. Medical insurance, corporate doctor visits and sports activities of your choice. 
Rest. Parties, team building, travel abroad and more.

